Source: oml-client
Section: net
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Christoph Dwertmann <christoph.dwertmann@nicta.com.au>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5), autoconf, automake, libtool, pkg-config, ruby, libpopt-dev, libtrace3-dev, libsigar-dev, liboml-dev (>= 2.3.4)
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: oml-client
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libsigar, libpopt0, liboml (>= 2.3.4), libtrace3, libc6
Description: OML Client Applications
 A collection of applications that use the OML client library to
 collect measurements generated from a variety of different sources.
 iperf_oml2 is a version of the popular iperf tool modified to send
 measurements using OML; wlanconfig_oml2 provides WLAN information
 taken from the wlanconfig program; gps_oml2 records GPS position
 information from an external GPS device; trace_oml2 provides packet
 capture analysis from libtrace; and nmetrics_oml2 provides
 measurements of node statistics derived from libsigar.

Package: otg
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, libpopt0, liboml (>= 2.3.4), libc6
Description: Orbit Traffic Generator
 OTG provides an instrumented traffic source/sink pair, with
 measurement collection on the transmitted and received traffic
 streams using OML.

